      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human review is needed because the remaining blockers are contributor-side real behavior proof, canonical PR selection, and maintainer acceptance of a process-wide egress-boundary change.; Needs attention: The diff is supply-chain clean, but it changes process-wide outbound proxy-bypass decisions and needs explicit network-boundary handling before merge. (sha=506d49129918a59a2e1f1928f40326c2f47c4f85)",
      "review_summary": "The PR wraps global EnvHttpProxyAgent construction with an OpenClaw NO_PROXY-aware dispatcher and changes lowercase no_proxy precedence in the shared matcher.\n\nPR surface: Source +129, Tests +82. Total +211 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: no. high-confidence live reproduction was established in this review. Source inspection and the linked issue logs show a credible global EnvHttpProxyAgent path, but the PR still lacks redacted current-main failure plus same-case branch success output.",
